COMPONENT NAME: JKM DB2 UDB Simple
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Knowledge Journalizing Module - This JKM provides simple journalizing procedures on IBM DB2 UDB tables - The following objects are created: - Subscribers central table - Journal table - Trigger on the journalized table that tracks the data changes in the Journal table - Views for selecting data
Restrictions: - This Knowledge Module creates triggers on your source tables. Be sure to validate the scalability of your applications before releasing your developments in your production systems.
Alter subscribers table for V3 comp

alter table <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> add JRN_ROW_COUNT <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%> add JRN_DATA_CMD <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%> add JRN_COUNT_CMD <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>

import java.sql as sql import java.lang as lang
# Connect to the Source Database ie the one that hosts the journalized tables myCon = odiRef.getJDBCConnection("SRC")
# Create the list of Subscribers for a CDC Set lstSbs = [] <%= odiRef.getSubscriberList("" , "lstSbs.append('[SUBSCRIBER]')", "\n", "") %>
ALTER TABLE <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> ALTER JRN_SUBSCRIBER SET DATA TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>

create table <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> ( JRN_TNAME <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "150")%> not null, JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%> not null, JRN_REFDATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE")%>, JRN_ROW_COUNT <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_NUMERIC", "20")%>, JRN_DATA_CMD <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>, JRN_COUNT_CMD <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>, constraint PK_SNP_JRN_SBS primary key (JRN_TNAME, JRN_SUBSCRIBER) )

insCmd = """ insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> (JRN_TNAME, JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_REFDATE, JRN_ROW_COUNT, JRN_DATA_CMD, JRN_COUNT_CMD) values ('<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>', ?, current timestamp, 0, null, 'update <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> set JRN_ROW_COUNT=(select count(''X'') from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> where JRN_SUBSCRIBER=''$$SUBSCRIBER_NAME$$'') where JRN_SUBSCRIBER=''$$SUBSCRIBER_NAME$$'' and JRN_TNAME=''<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>''') """
selCmd = """ select count('X') from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> where JRN_SUBSCRIBER = ? and JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' """
# Prepare the statements prepInsStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(insCmd) prepSelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(selCmd)
# Execute for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepSelStmt.setString(1, sbs) rs = prepSelStmt.executeQuery() rs.next() nbSubs = rs.getInt(1) if (nbSubs == 0): prepInsStmt.setString(1, sbs) nbRows = prepInsStmt.executeUpdate()
prepInsStmt.close() prepSelStmt.close()
# Commit the updates myCon.commit()
ALTER TABLE <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> ALTER JRN_SUBSCRIBER SET DATA TYPE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%>

create table <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> /* This table is created in the work physical schema of the current Data server */ ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "400")%> not null, JRN_CONSUMED <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1")%>, JRN_FLAG <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_VARCHAR", "1")%>, JRN_DATE <%=odiRef.getDataType("DEST_DATE")%>, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]\t[DEST_WRI_DT] default null", ",\n\t", "", "(PK)")%> )

create view <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_VIEW")%> /* This view is created in the work physical schema of the current Data server */ as select case when (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "char(TARG.[COL_NAME])", " || ", "", "PK")%> is null) then 'D' else 'I' end <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_FLAG, JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN.JRN_DATE <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]		" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "PK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "TARG.[COL_NAME]		" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "NOT PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN left outer join <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> TARG on ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "TARG.[COL_NAME]	= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "PK")%> ) where JRN.JRN_DATE = ( select max(L.JRN_DATE) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> L where L.JRN_CONSUMED = '1' and L.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "L.[COL_NAME]	= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "
				and	", "", "PK")%> )

create view <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_DATA_VIEW")%> /* This view is created in the work physical schema of the current Data server */ as select case when (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "char(TARG.[COL_NAME])", " || ", "", "PK")%> is null) then 'D' else 'I' end <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_FLAG, JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN.JRN_DATE <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "JRN.[COL_NAME]		" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "PK")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "TARG.[COL_NAME]		" + odiRef.getInfo("DEST_COL_ALIAS_WORD") + " [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "NOT PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> JRN left outer join <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> TARG on ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "TARG.[COL_NAME]	= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "PK")%> ) where JRN.JRN_DATE = ( select max(L.JRN_DATE) from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> <%= odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> L where L.JRN_SUBSCRIBER = JRN.JRN_SUBSCRIBER and <%=odiRef.getColList("", "L.[COL_NAME]	= JRN.[COL_NAME]", "
				and	", "", "PK")%> )

create trigger <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_ITRIGGER")%> after insert on <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> referencing NEW as NROW for each row mode db2sql insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_CONSUMED, JRN_FLAG, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) select JRN_SUBSCRIBER, '0', 'I', current timestamp, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "NROW.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> where JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' /* The following line can be uncommented for symetric replication */ /* and upper(USER) <> upper('<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_USER_NAME")%>') */

create trigger <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_UTRIGGER")%> after update on <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> referencing NEW as NROW for each row mode db2sql insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_CONSUMED, JRN_FLAG, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) select JRN_SUBSCRIBER, '0', 'I', current timestamp, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "NROW.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> where JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' /* The following line can be uncommented for symetric replication */ /* and upper(USER) <> upper('<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_USER_NAME")%>') */

create trigger <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_DTRIGGER")%> after delete on <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%> referencing OLD as OROW for each row mode db2sql insert into <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> ( JRN_SUBSCRIBER, JRN_CONSUMED, JRN_FLAG, JRN_DATE, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> ) select JRN_SUBSCRIBER, '0', 'D', current timestamp, <%=odiRef.getColList("", "OROW.[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t\t", "", "PK")%> from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> where JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' /* The following line can be uncommented for symetric replication */ /* and upper(USER) <> upper('<%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_USER_NAME")%>') */

delCmd = """ delete from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("JRN_FULL_NAME")%> where JRN_SUBSCRIBER = ? """
# Prepare the delete prepDelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(delCmd)
# Execute it for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepDelStmt.setString(1, sbs) nbRows = prepDelStmt.executeUpdate()
prepDelStmt.close()
# Commit updates myCon.commit()

delCmd = """ delete from <%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("SNP_JRN_SUBSCRIBER")%> where JRN_SUBSCRIBER = ? and JRN_TNAME = '<%=odiRef.getJrnInfo("FULL_TABLE_NAME")%>' """
# Prepare the delete prepDelStmt = myCon.prepareStatement(delCmd)
# Execute it for each subscriber for sbs in lstSbs: prepDelStmt.setString(1, sbs) nbRows = prepDelStmt.executeUpdate()
prepDelStmt.close()
# Commit the updates myCon.commit()
